chapter-1/skr3/func.html.title: SKR-3 function definition
chapter-1/skr3/func.html.body:
2.SKR-3 Firmware Compilation
1.Firmware Compilation

After ssh is connected to raspberry pie, enter at the command line：

​     cd ~/klipper/.
​     make menuconfig.
​     [\] Enable extra low-level configuration options 
​    * Micro-controller Architecture (STMicroelectronics STM32) ---> 
​    * Processor model (STM32H743) ---> 
​    * Bootloader offset (128KB bootloader (SKR SE BX v2.0)) ---> 
​    * Clock Reference (25 MHz crystal) ---> 
​    * Communication interface (USB (on PA11/PA12)) ---> 


After the configuration is selected, enter 'q' to exit the configuration interface. When asked whether to save the configuration, select "Yes"


Enter make to compile the firmware. When the make is completed, it will be displayed in the raspberry pie home/pi/kliipper/out file.The folder generates the klipper we need Bin firmware, which can be directly downloaded to the computer on the left side of the ssh software




Replace klipper Rename bin as "firmware. bin", and copy it to the SD card to update the firmware


在命令行输入： ls /dev/serial/by-id/.Query the ID of the motherboard to confirm whether the firmware is successfully burned,If the burning is successful, a klipper device ID will be returned, as shown in the following figure


​        Copy and save this ID, which needs to be set in the configuration file
2.Configure Klipper

Enter the IP access of Raspberry Pie in the computer browser, and download the reference configuration of the motherboard in the path shown below,If this file cannot be found, please update the Klipepr firmware source code to the latest version, or download it from githubhttps://github.com/bigtreetech/SKR-3 



Upload the configuration file of the motherboard to Configuration Files and rename it as "printer. cfg"



Modify the ID number in the configuration file to the actual ID of the motherboard



According to  https://www.klipper3d.org/Overview.html  Description of Configuring the specific functions of the machine

chapter-2/Klipper/Klipper.html.body:
1、Klipper
1.1 Preparation
1.1.1 Download system image
Download the system image of the built-in WebUI you like. Currently, the mainstream includes Fluidd, Mainmail, etc.
Built in Fluidd system: https://github.com/fluidd-core/FluiddPI/releases

Built in Mainsail  system: https://github.com/mainsail-crew/MainsailOS/releases

Or refer to Klipper's official installation instructions to use Octoprint
1.1.2 Download and install Raspberry Pi Imager
Download and install the official burning software of Raspberry Pie  https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/ 
1.2 Burn Image
 1.Insert the Micro SD card reader into the computer.
 2.Select System.
  ![image-photo3](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/z1996xm/gitbook-demo/master/photo/photo3.jpg) 

Select "User defined", and then select the image downloaded to the computer.
 

Select the SD card to be burned (burning the image will format the SD card. Be careful not to select the wrong drive letter, or it will

Format data on other storage), click "Burn".
 

Wait for the burning to complete.

 


1.3 Set WIFI
Note: If you use the network cable port instead of WIFI, you can skip this step

Reseat the card reader

Find the "fluiddpi-wpa-supplicant.txt" or "mainmail-wpa supplicant.txt" file in the boot disk of the SD card and open it with VSCode (do not open it with the notepad that comes with Windows)


Delete the '#' character at the beginning of the four lines in the red box, and set the correct WIFI name and password before saving



1.4 Connecting raspberry pie with ssh software

Install the ssh software Mobaxterm:https://mobaxterm.mobatek.net/download-home-edition.html 

Insert the SD card into the raspberry pie, and wait for the system to start after power on, about 1-2 minutes

The raspberry pie will be automatically assigned an IP after it is connected to WIFI or plugged into the Internet cable

Enter the router management interface to find the IP address of Raspberry Pie


Or use https://angryip.org/ Tool, scan all IP addresses under the current LAN, and use the



Reorder the machine names, and find the devices whose host names are Fluidd or Mainmail, as shown in the following figure

Open the installed Mobaxterm software, click "Session", click "SSH" in the pop-up window, enter the IP address of raspberry pie in the Remote host column, and click "OK" (Note: computers and raspberry pie must Under the same LAN)



Enter login as: pi login password: raspberry to enter the SSH terminal interface
